_source.body:
A proposed bill prohibiting New York City landlords from conducting criminal background checks on prospective tenants appears to be on track to become law.

The “Fair Chance for Housing Act,” or Intro. 632, has the support of at least 30 of the 51 city council members, while Mayor Eric Adams (D) has signaled a willingness to sign the bill.

“No one should be denied housing because they were once engaged with the criminal justice system, plain and simple,” said Adam’s spokesman Charles Lutvack via the New York Post.

PAUL SPERRY BLOWS WHISTLE ON CORRUPT SPECIAL COUNSEL JACK SMITH: “Ironically, just-appointed Special Counsel Jack Smith was at the center of an Obama administration scandal even many Democrats clamored for a special counsel to investigate.

In 2014, the House passed a bipartisan resolution calling on then-Attorney General Eric Holder to appoint a special counsel to investigate the IRS targeting of conservative non-profit groups. Smith involved the Justice Dept in the illegal targeting. That resolution to name a special counsel to investigate the IRS and DOJ -- including then-DOJ official Jack Smith, an Obama official -- was supported by 26 Democrats.” (11/27/22)
